[Phase 3 — New Logic Files]

app/engines/suppression_filter.py: (new file)
  Functions:
    load_suppression_config()    — reads admin_config.json layer8_filters, falls back to hardcoded defaults
    check_time_of_day(config)    — blocks signals during configured lunch/chop windows
    check_symbol_cooldown(symbol, direction, config) — enforces per-symbol+direction cooldown via signals table
    check_sector_cap(symbol, config) — caps concurrent WATCHING/ACTIVE trades per sector
    check_daily_cap(config)      — enforces max_trades_per_day via trades table count
    check_daily_trend_veto(symbol, direction, config, kite_client) — vetoes CALLs when daily close < EMA (cached 300s)
    log_suppression(...)         — appends CSV row to ~/nse-fno-screener-data/suppression_log.csv
  Sector map covers 100+ F&O symbols across 15 sector buckets.
  Indices (NIFTY, BANKNIFTY, etc.) have sector="Index" and are exempt from sector cap.

app/screener.py: wired 5 suppression checks post-Layer-6
  - Added _get_layer3_min_score() helper (reads admin_config.json, default 60)
  - layer3_min for non-index candidates now reads from admin_config.json (was hardcoded 45)
  - After signal generation (if signal:), all 5 suppression checks run before
    signals.append() and paper_trader.on_signal()
